  <div class="container">  
  <div class="row">

    <% var active='welcome'; %>
    <% include ./partials/sidebar %>
      
      <div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9">
      <div class="content">
        <div class="hero-unit">
           <div class="modal fade" id="ShowContactForm" role="dialog">
                <div class="modal-dialog">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                    <h4 class="modal-title">Experience a MongoDB deployment!</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                    <h3>MongoDB</h3>
                    <h4>A general purpose database for modern applications</h4>
                    <p>Most of the data today is non-structured and does not fit neatly into rows, columns and tables referenced with constraints. With over 21 Million downloads, <a href="http://db-engines.com/en/ranking" target="_">MongoDB is the world's most popular open source document oriented database.</a> Built upon its foundation of addressing non-structured data, MongoDB goes far beyond just storing and retrieving data. In fact, with MongoDB you can perform advanced analytics queries like faceted, graph, and geospatial based searches natively without needing any third party software.  Coupled with management tools like <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/products/ops-manager" target="_">OpsManager</a>, <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/products/compass" target="_">Compass</a> and a follow the sun support model from MongoDB it’s no surprise that companies are migrating their existing everyday relational database applications with MongoDB!</p>

                    <h4>This website allows you to explore MongoDB features interactively</h4>
                    <p>Pre-loaded with a business review database, this website allows you to explore many key capabilities that showcase MongoDB's multi-model approach to data management.  Written from a perspective of someone familiar with relational database technologies you will not only discover some of the key enhancements with MongoDB, you will learn the MongoDB equivalent of joins, views, and constraints.</p>
                    <p>To experience these capabilities now, please tell us a little about yourself:</p>
                    <label for="inputEmailAddress">Business email:</label><br>
                    <input type="text" class="form-control" id="inputEmailAddress" placeholder="Enter business email address" >
                     <div id="msgEmailIssue" style="display:none"><p class="text-danger">Please provide a valid email address.</p></div><br>
                    <label for="ddHaveProject">Do you have a MongoDB project?</label><br>
                    
                     <select class="form-control" id="ddHaveProject" required>
                      <option value="Yes">Yes</option>
                      <option value="No">No</option>
                      <option value="Not Yet" selected="true">Not Yet</option>
                      </select><br>
                      <label for="ddUseCase">What's your use case?</label><br>
                      <select class="form-control" id="ddUseCase" required>
                         <option value="Catalog">Catalog</option>
                         <option value="Content Management">Content Management</option>
                         <option value="IOT">Internet of Things</option>
                         <option value="Mobile">Mobile</option>
                         <option value="Personalization">Personalization</option>
                         <option value="analytics">Real Time analytics</option>
                         <option value="Side Project">Side Project</option>
                         <option value="Single View">Single View</option>
                         <option value="Datawarehouse">Datawarehouse</option>
                         <option value="Other" selected="true">Other</option>
                         </select><br>
                    
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-success" id="ContinueButton" onclick="ContinueTheTour()">Continue</button><br>
                   
            
                    </div>
                    <label id="lblErrorMessage"></label>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
